This paper deals with device-to-device (D2D) communications in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also proposes a framework for handling channel opportunities, which involves system-level optimization and protocols, making it relevant to systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper uses software-defined radio (SDR) to implement and test the proposed framework, which falls under multimedia (MM) and cryptography and security (CR) categories.
